  "local_port": 49436,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I change my Google default account?",
  "response": "Changing your default Google account can be useful if you want to switch to a different account for services like Gmail, YouTube, Google Drive, etc. Here's how you can do it:\n\n---\n\n### **On a Computer:**\n1. **Sign Out of All Accounts**:\n   - Go to [Google](https://www.google.com).\n   - Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner.\n   - Select **Sign out** or **Sign out of all accounts**.\n\n2. **Sign In with the Desired Default Account**:\n   - After signing out, sign back in with the account you want to set as the default.\n   - This will temporarily make it your default account.\n\n3. **Add Other Accounts**:\n   - Click on your profile picture again.\n   - Select **Add another account** to log in to your other Google accounts.\n   - Google will always prioritize the first account you signed in with as the default.\n\n---\n\n### **On Mobile (Android or iOS):**\n1. **Switch Accounts in the Google App**:\n   - Open the **Google** app (or any Google app like Gmail, YouTube, etc.).\n   - Tap your profile picture in the top-right corner.\n   - Select **Add another account** or **Use another account** to log in to the account you want to set as default.\n\n2. **Reorder Accounts**:\n   - Tap your profile picture again.\n   - Select **Manage accounts on this device**.\n   - Drag the account you want as default to the top of the list.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips:**\n- The **default account** is the first account you signed in with after signing out.\n- You can switch between accounts in any Google app by tapping your profile picture and selecting another account.\n- If you're using Chrome, you can manage accounts in **Settings > You and Google > Sync and Google services**.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
